ake your attempt to kill the target the day of spawn unless it spawns after 8:00 PM for your guild's local regional time (ex: EST/PST for USA, GMT+9 for Japan, GMT+1 for Euro). If it spawns after 8:00 p.m. local time, you should begin your attempt the next day within 24 hours of the target's spawn time. <P>2. If you're going to pass, do so within a reasonable amount of time. (before 5:00 PM local). On rotations where pass/fail is tracked, passing when you are currently up for the target counts as a failed attempt. <P>3. If a large target spawns 6-8 hours before patch or server maintenance, it MAY be considered FFA. The guild that is up for a target when a patch is imminent may NOT declare the target FFA and then engage the target. The guild up for the target MUST make an attempt to find a swap if they are not going to engage the target. <P>In the case of a FFA god, the guild scheduled to be in the plane the day/night before patch can kill the god if they are able to, or call in another guild to kill the god. The "god" group may help them clear spawn with the understanding that all planar loot goes to the "plane" guild and all god loot goes to the "god" guild. <P>Use your judgement. We have been handling these rare FFA situations relatively fine for close to two years now. If you think you are going to be flamed for your actions by a good portion of the KGC members, it is probably an abuse of the FFA rules.<P>4. There should be no help from ANY members of other guilds/alliances for large targets if their guild/alliance occupies a spot within that particular large target rotation. (this does not apply to Vox/Nag due to level restrictions). <P>Example: Do not accept or solicit help from anyone in the Inny rotation if you are killing Inny. If you are killing Trakanon, getting help from another guild/alliance in the Inny or Vox rotation is okay as long as they are not in the Trakanon rotation. Keep all help such as this to a minimum as it is the spirit of the KGC that each guild occupying a slot does so because they are able to do it on their own and understands the concept behind having a rotation. It is all about being equal and therefore sharing equally. Having 1-2 groups but gathering 4-5 more groups in various other guilds/alliances would be considered abuse. <P>5. The guild that is up for Cazic Thule may enter the Plane of Fear after 8:00 p.m. to help clear the plane so they can kill the god. They are strongly encouraged to work with the guild that has the plane to set up a time they may enter. Note: All drops from regular mobs, mini-bosses and the dracoliche go to the guild that had the plane scheduled for the day.<P>6. Post the results of the large target attempt on the KGC ASAP (pass/fail/success) so the next guild can prepare for their turn. It is customary to post the loot obtained. <P>7. Kunark Outdoor dragons follow a progressive scale of Sev -&gt; Tal -&gt; Gor. You need to kill Severillous before entering Talendor rotation, Talendor before entering Gorenaire rotation. An additional option to get on the Tal/Gor rotations is without outside assistance to kill any of the following: Wuoshi, Klandicar, Sontalak or any of the named ToV dragons.<P>8. If you pass/fail on Nagafen, Lady Vox, Severillous, Talendor, Gorenaire, Venril Sathir, Trakanon or any rotation target 2 times in a row you will drop out of the rotation for 1 cycle. Your pass/fail count will be designated in parentheses beside your slot in the rotation. <P>9. Do not kill fire giants on server reset unless you are up for Nagafen. Do not kill fire giants AT ALL if Nagafen is up. <P>10. The prerequisite for joining the Yelinak rotation is killing (with no outside assistance) one of the following: Kland, Sont, Keeper.<P>NToV Rules/Rotation:<P>1) NTOV, with the exception of Eeshan and Indy is on a rotation. Although Indy and Eeshan are typically, FFA, guilds must step aside when the NTOV rotation guild arrives for their turn with at least 30 people.<P>2) Aary must be killed on the first night and must be killed before doing any NToV rotation dragons. If a guild does not kill Aary on the first night, their turn is over, and they go to the back on the rotation. THe next guild in the rotation is then up.<P>3) If a guild fails two times in a row on Aary, they get a (skip).<P>4) The rotation slot for NToV can last for up to three days. At least one dragon must be killed each day. <P>5) If a guild completes their slot or gives up prior to the end of their slot the remainder of the zone is FFA till Aary repops or the next patch, whichever comes first.<P>6) If Aary pops but the remainder of the zone hasnt spawned the guild up shall be allowed 48 hour delay in starting time to allow for full pop, but once they start their time has started<P>7) To add their name to the NToV rotation a guild must be able to (without outside help) kill Cazic Thule and Keeper or Yelinak.<P><BR>[This message has been edited by Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst (edited 04-09-2002).]<P>[This message has been edited by Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst (edited 05-07-2002).]<P>[This message has been edited by Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst (edited 05-13-2002).]<P>[This message has been edited by Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst (edited 07-01-2002).]<p>[This message has been edited by Kellory (edited 01-20-2003).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
